{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17502430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17502430"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:43:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:43:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1861"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1861","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1861"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.75,0.11,0.03,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1861"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115850"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1861","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1861"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1861"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97850"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"6376"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3503"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3614"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27697"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44348"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49198"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115850"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a two-day history of right-sided abdominal pain, anorexia and vomiting. She reports four days of urinary frequency and burning prior to this. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. Her last menstrual period was two weeks ago and she denies any gynaecological symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 96/min, blood pressure 110/75 mmHg, respiratory rate 20/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 38.4\u00b0C. Her abdomen is soft with tenderness in the right flank and right iliac fossa. Urinalysis shows microscopic haematuria and pyuria. A CT scan is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acute diverticulitis","Acute pyelonephritis","Renal abscess","Psoas abscess","Appendix abscess"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of \u003Cstrong\u003Eacute pyelonephritis\u003C/strong\u003E: fever, flank pain, and preceding lower urinary tract symptoms. The urinalysis findings of pyuria and haematuria, along with CT findings of perinephric stranding (see figure below), support this diagnosis. Pyelonephritis typically develops from an ascending urinary tract infection, as seen in this case with the preceding urinary frequency and dysuria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcute diverticulitis\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with left-sided abdominal pain, though right-sided diverticulitis can occur. The presence of urinary symptoms and urinalysis findings make this diagnosis less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Erenal abscess\u003C/strong\u003E can present similarly to pyelonephritis with fever, flank pain, and urinary symptoms. However, CT imaging would show a well-defined mass with thick, irregular walls rather than the perinephric stranding seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epsoas abscess\u003C/strong\u003E would demonstrate a fluid collection in the retrofascial space on CT imaging. The presence of urinary symptoms and urinalysis findings make this diagnosis unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eappendix abscess\u003C/strong\u003E, while potentially causing right-sided abdominal pain and fever, would show a fluid collection around the appendix on CT. The preceding urinary symptoms and supportive urinalysis findings point away from this diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute pyelonephritis typically presents with fever, flank pain, and urinary symptoms following an ascending urinary tract infection","Urinalysis showing pyuria and haematuria supports the diagnosis of pyelonephritis","CT findings of perinephric stranding are characteristic of acute pyelonephritis"],"references":["Craig WD, Wagner BJ, Travis MD. Pyelonephritis: radiologic-pathologic review. Radiographics. 2008 Jan;28(1):255-76."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97850"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1861"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18362"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"22138"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18362","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18362"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/99153bc9-fbdb-4de9-975c-add893acdee2.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/99153bc9-fbdb-4de9-975c-add893acdee2.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":503,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"22138","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/22138"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/yj7BGEjp5yo9soshQTutcTPRo9fKb5.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/yj7BGEjp5yo9soshQTutcTPRo9fKb5.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":503,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97850"},"attributes":{"c